OL,4,CGreater Manchester Police chief
OL,5,Cconstable rejects taking the knee
OL,6, Greater Manchester Police's new chief
OL,7, constable has said he "absolutely would
OL,8, not" take the knee in uniform as it
OL,9, could undermine impartiality.
OL,11,FStephen Watson told the Daily Telegraph
OL,12,Fhe "would probably kneel before the
OL,13,FQueen, God, and Mrs Watson, that's it".
OL,15,FHe also said he was concerned about the
OL,16,Fcreation of new "hate crimes" which
OL,17,Fcould overwhelm police as they "sought
OL,18,Fto criminalise what people think".
OL,20,FMr Watson joined the force, which is in
OL,21,Fspecial measures, in May.
